# __APPA_PROJECT_NAME__

An Appa instance. Generic chat-with-tutor-plus-team-workspace, customized for this project.

## Run

```bash
cp .env.example .env  # set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
npm install
npm start
```

Then open <http://127.0.0.1:3848>.

## Files

- `appa.config.js` — which modules to load and runtime settings
- `team.json` — your roster (coaches + members)
- `tutor-prompt.md` — the tutor persona (edit this to fit your domain)
- `shared-memory.md` — knowledge the tutor sees in every session

Data files are created lazily as modules are used (`tasks.json`, `photos.json`, `transcripts/`, etc.).

## Adding a module

Create `modules/my-module.js` exporting an [AppaModule](https://github.com/karl-kahn/appa#modules), then import it in `appa.config.js`:

```js
import myModule from "./modules/my-module.js";
// ...
export default defineConfig({
  modules: [tasks, photos, activity, myModule],
});
```
